	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=251249><span id= >Ktok</span></a><br><span id=notbold>41 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>These are the top of the line agro combos for a Warrior. Period.<br><br>For tanking non-riposte happy mobs:<br><br>Primary: Bloodfrenzy + Anger III<br>Secondary: Hategiver + Anger II<br><br>For tanking pre-Elemental bosses:<br><br>Primary: Bloodfrenzy + Anger III<br>Secondary: Furious Bash shield, such as Stormrider Carapace or Zek Crested Buckler.<br><br>For tanking Elemental Bosses, pre-Earth:<br><br>Blade of War<br><br>For tanking post-Earth, prior to getting the Darkblade of the Warlord from Zek in PoTime:<br><br>Trash Mobs:<br>Primary: Bloodfrenzy + Anger III<br>Secondary: Aegis of the Earth<br><br>Gods:<br>Blade of War<br><br>Ultimate Quarm tanking combo:<br><br>Primary: Darkblade of the Warlord + Anger III (from Radiant Marble Sphere of Ire to match the Darkblade’s Type 8 slot)<br>Secondary: Shield of Strife<br>Chest: Raex's Chestplate of Destruction (for Echo of Anger effect)<br><br>Remember, tanking is all about generating hate and taking hits, not doing damage. This combo provides you with the best hate generation, a slower attack speed (to cut down on the ripostes from the gods) and huge AC.<br><br>Granted, these are all pie in the sky best case scenarios that most will likely never see, but it you’re going to talk tanking equipment, you might as well go all out, right? &lt;grin&gt;<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Ktok Th'Rooks<br>Leader of &lt;Portent Alliance&gt;<br>Firiona Vie Server</td></tr>
